associatedDiagnosis.description: Hypertension secondary to renal disease, with delivery, with current postpartum complication

narrative: PROCEDURE: MRA HEAD WO CONTRAST - , 7/9/2014 2:48 PM
ACCESSION NUMBER(S): AFM14001638
LOCATION: OPLOC
COMPARISON: None
CLINICAL INDICATION: CRAO right, CVA.
TECHNIQUE:
Noncontrast 3-D time-of-flight MRA of the intracranial
circulation performed with maximum intensity projections in
multiple projections.
FINDINGS:
Mild narrowing of the left greater than right supraclinoid ICAs.
Otherwise no significant large vessel stenosis or occlusion. No
aneurysms or vascular malformation.
IMPRESSION:
Mild stenosis of the supraclinoid internal carotid arteries left
greater than right.
Otherwise normal MRI of the intracranial circulation.
CLINICAL INDICATION:  Chest pressure when supine.
DICTATION TIME: 03/06/09, 1326 hours
TECHNIQUE:  Helical acquisition through the chest and abdomen.
Images reconstructed at 1.25 and 2.5-mm collimation in soft
tissue windows as well as 5-mm collimation for lung windows.
Sagittal and coronal reformatted images were obtained.
FINDINGS:  Shotty axillary lymph nodes. Shotty mediastinal lymph
nodes. Cardiomegaly is present. No definite axillary, hilar, or
mediastinal adenopathy. No pleural or pericardial fluid
collection. There is good opacification of pulmonary
vasculature. The examination is somewhat by patient motion
artifact through the chest. No definite pulmonary embolism or
dissection. Lung windows reveal subpleural emphysematous
changes. A partially calcified nodule is indeterminate. Follow
up is recommended. Scattered areas of pleural parenchymal
scarring. No nodule or endobronchial lesion. No definite
abdominal aortic aneurysm or dissection. Patulous origin of the
common origin of the superior mesenteric and celiac arteries.
Small hiatal hernia with elevation of the left hemidiaphragm. A
small accessory splenic nodule measuring in the range of 8-mm is
noted at the level of the splenic hilum. Remainder of the
visualized solid abdominal viscera appear intact. Scattered
colonic diverticula without signs of diverticulitis. No biliary
tree dilation. Sagittal and coronal reformatted images were
reviewed. Bone windows reveal scoliotic curvature and
degenerative disk disease. There are mild sclerotic endplate
changes present. No aggressive lytic or sclerotic lesion
appreciated.
IMPRESSION:
1.     No definite pulmonary embolism or dissection.
2.     Faint calcification is noted within a right lower lobe
pulmonary nodule, which measures 6-mm. This is likely
granulomatous in nature though would recommend six month
follow up.
3.     Scoliotic curvature and degenerative disk disease.
4.     No abdominal aortic aneurysm.
5.     Diverticulosis without signs of diverticulitis.
6.     Hiatal hernia.
7.     Facts report was sent to the emergency department at the
time of dictation.
